## Summary

With `link_resolution.global_basename=true`, a **bare** wikilink like `[[struktura]]` outside the DIR_PATTERN whitelist resolves through the generic pass (issue #972). But the **path-qualified** form `[[notes/struktura]]` (any dir not in DIR_PATTERN) produces **zero edges** on the DB path (`extract links --source db` and `put_page` auto-link) — while the FS path resolves the identical content. The drop is silent: no unresolved report, no log line.

## Repro (PGLite, no DATABASE_URL needed)

```ts
await engine.putPage('notes/struktura', {
  type: 'concept', title: 'Struktura Notes', compiled_truth: '', timeline: '',
});
await engine.putPage('concepts/knowledge-graph', {
  type: 'concept', title: 'Knowledge Graph',
  compiled_truth: 'Background in [[notes/struktura]].', timeline: '',
});
await engine.setConfig('link_resolution.global_basename', 'true');

await runExtract(engine, ['links', '--source', 'db']);

const links = await engine.getLinks('concepts/knowledge-graph');
// EXPECTED: one wikilink_basename edge → notes/struktura
// ACTUAL (before this fix): [] — silently dropped
```

Same content on disk via the FS extractor (`runExtract(engine, ['links', '--dir', dir])`) emits the edge.

## Root cause

`extractPageLinks` (src/core/link-extraction.ts) forwards the **raw literal** to the resolver:

```ts
const matches = await resolver.resolveBasenameMatches(ref.slug); // ref.slug = "notes/struktura"
```

`resolveBasenameMatches` → `queryBasenameIndex` looks up an index **keyed by final path segments** (raw → lower → slugified), so any slash-containing literal misses every key.

The FS path already handles this — `resolveSlugAll` (src/commands/extract.ts) strips the dirname before its basename lookup, and its comment documents `[[notes/struktura]]` as a supported form:

```ts
// Strip .md suffix + dirname so `[[struktura]]` (relTarget=`struktura.md`)
// and `[[notes/struktura]]` (relTarget=`notes/struktura.md`) both query
// for the basename `struktura`.
```

## What this PR does

Query the basename index by the literal's **final segment** — mirroring the FS path — and use the written path as a **disambiguation filter**: a match must end with the literal, so `[[notes/struktura]]` can resolve to `vault/notes/struktura` but never attach to `wiki/struktura`. The filter is the DB-path analogue of the FS ancestor walk honoring the written path before falling back to the bare basename.

Bare literals (`[[struktura]]`) are untouched — `slashIdx === -1` short-circuits to the existing behavior. Flag-gated as before: nothing changes unless `link_resolution.global_basename=true`.

## Scope

- One branch in `extractPageLinks` (src/core/link-extraction.ts). Engine-agnostic core — the same code path serves the postgres and pglite engines, `extract links --source db`, and `put_page` auto-link.
- FS path untouched.

## Measured impact

On one of our brains (1,650 pages): 246 of 1,332 wikilink occurrences (18%) were silently dropped — all path-qualified refs to non-DIR_PATTERN dirs. With this fix, a single `extract links --source db` rescan connected 175 edges retroactively; every remaining miss is accounted for (target absent, cross-source, or wikilink inside a code span).

Related: #1493 (broad report on the DIR_PATTERN whitelist), #972 (the generic pass this bug lives in).

## Tests

- 4 unit tests (test/link-extraction.test.ts): dirname-strip lookup, written-path filter, deeper-slug suffix match, path-qualified self-link drop.
- 2 e2e tests (test/e2e/global-basename-pglite.test.ts, DB-source describe): path-qualified resolution end-to-end + sibling exclusion.
- R1–R4 clean: no env mutation, no mock.module, reuses the file's canonical engine block, no allowlist entries.

`bun run verify` passes (31/31 checks). Full unit suite: 9,751 pass / 8 fail — the 8 are workstation-environment serial tests (git-hook env, `OPENAI_API_KEY` present) that fail identically on unpatched master with this change stashed; none touch link extraction.

